{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"So since I was here last in '06,"},{"time":4000,"text":"we discovered that global climate change"},{"time":6000,"text":"is turning out to be a pretty serious issue,"},{"time":8000,"text":"so we covered that fairly extensively"},{"time":10000,"text":"in Skeptic magazine."},{"time":12000,"text":"We investigate all kinds"},{"time":14000,"text":"of scientific and quasi-scientific controversies,"},{"time":17000,"text":"but it turns out we don't have to worry about any of this"},{"time":19000,"text":"because the world's going to end in 2012."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21000,"text":"Another update:"},{"time":23000,"text":"You will recall I introduced you guys"},{"time":25000,"text":"to the Quadro Tracker."},{"time":27000,"text":"It's like a water dowsing device."},{"time":29000,"text":"It's just a hollow piece of plastic with an antenna that swivels around."},{"time":32000,"text":"And you walk around, and it points to things."},{"time":34000,"text":"Like if you're looking for marijuana in students' lockers,"},{"time":37000,"text":"it'll point right to somebody."},{"time":39000,"text":"Oh, sorry. (Laughter)"},{"time":41000,"text":"This particular one that was given to me"},{"time":43000,"text":"finds golf balls,"},{"time":45000,"text":"especially if you're at a golf course"},{"time":47000,"text":"and you check under enough bushes."},{"time":50000,"text":"Well, under the category of \"What's the harm of silly stuff like this?\""},{"time":53000,"text":"this device, the ADE 651,"},{"time":56000,"text":"was sold to the Iraqi government"},{"time":59000,"text":"for 40,000 dollars apiece."},{"time":61000,"text":"It's just like this one, completely worthless,"},{"time":63000,"text":"in which it allegedly worked by \"electrostatic"},{"time":65000,"text":"magnetic ion attraction,\""},{"time":69000,"text":"which translates to"},{"time":71000,"text":"\"pseudoscientific baloney\" -- would be the nice word --"},{"time":74000,"text":"in which you string together a bunch of words that sound good,"},{"time":76000,"text":"but it does absolutely nothing."},{"time":78000,"text":"In this case, at trespass points,"},{"time":81000,"text":"allowing people to go through"},{"time":83000,"text":"because your little tracker device said they were okay,"},{"time":86000,"text":"actually cost lives."},{"time":89000,"text":"So there is a danger to pseudoscience,"},{"time":91000,"text":"in believing in this sort of thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94000,"text":"So what I want to talk about today is belief."},{"time":97000,"text":"I want to believe,"},{"time":99000,"text":"and you do too."},{"time":101000,"text":"And in fact, I think my thesis here is that"},{"time":103000,"text":"belief is the natural state of things."},{"time":105000,"text":"It is the default option. We just believe."},{"time":107000,"text":"We believe all sorts of things."},{"time":109000,"text":"Belief is natural;"},{"time":111000,"text":"disbelief, skepticism, science, is not natural."},{"time":113000,"text":"It's more difficult."},{"time":115000,"text":"It's uncomfortable to not believe things."},{"time":117000,"text":"So like Fox Mulder on \"X-Files,\""},{"time":120000,"text":"who wants to believe in UFOs? Well, we all do,"},{"time":123000,"text":"and the reason for that is because"},{"time":125000,"text":"we have a belief engine in our brains."},{"time":128000,"text":"Essentially, we are pattern-seeking primates."},{"time":131000,"text":"We connect the dots: A is connected to B; B is connected to C."},{"time":134000,"text":"And sometimes A really is connected to B,"},{"time":137000,"text":"and that's called association learning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139000,"text":"We find patterns, we make those connections,"},{"time":142000,"text":"whether it's Pavlov's dog here"},{"time":144000,"text":"associating the sound of the bell with the food,"},{"time":147000,"text":"and then he salivates to the sound of the bell,"},{"time":149000,"text":"or whether it's a Skinnerian rat,"},{"time":151000,"text":"in which he's having an association"},{"time":153000,"text":"between his behavior and a reward for it,"},{"time":155000,"text":"and therefore he repeats the behavior."},{"time":157000,"text":"In fact, what Skinner discovered"},{"time":159000,"text":"is that, if you put a pigeon in a box like this,"},{"time":162000,"text":"and he has to press one of these two keys,"},{"time":164000,"text":"and he tries to figure out what the pattern is,"},{"time":166000,"text":"and you give him a little reward in the hopper box there --"},{"time":168000,"text":"if you just randomly assign rewards"},{"time":171000,"text":"such that there is no pattern,"},{"time":173000,"text":"they will figure out any kind of pattern."},{"time":175000,"text":"And whatever they were doing just before they got the reward,"},{"time":177000,"text":"they repeat that particular pattern."},{"time":179000,"text":"Sometimes it was even spinning around twice counterclockwise,"},{"time":182000,"text":"once clockwise and peck the key twice."},{"time":185000,"text":"And that's called superstition,"},{"time":187000,"text":"and that, I'm afraid,"},{"time":189000,"text":"we will always have with us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":191000,"text":"I call this process \"patternicity\" --"},{"time":193000,"text":"that is, the tendency to find meaningful patterns"},{"time":195000,"text":"in both meaningful and meaningless noise."},{"time":198000,"text":"When we do this process, we make two types of errors."},{"time":201000,"text":"A Type I error, or false positive,"},{"time":203000,"text":"is believing a pattern is real"},{"time":205000,"text":"when it's not."},{"time":207000,"text":"Our second type of error is a false negative."},{"time":209000,"text":"A Type II error is not believing"},{"time":211000,"text":"a pattern is real when it is."},{"time":214000,"text":"So let's do a thought experiment."},{"time":216000,"text":"You are a hominid three million years ago"},{"time":218000,"text":"walking on the plains of Africa."},{"time":221000,"text":"Your name is Lucy, okay?"},{"time":223000,"text":"And you hear a rustle in the grass."},{"time":225000,"text":"Is it a dangerous predator,"},{"time":227000,"text":"or is it just the wind?"},{"time":229000,"text":"Your next decision could be the most important one of your life."},{"time":232000,"text":"Well, if you think that the rustle in the grass is a dangerous predator"},{"time":235000,"text":"and it turns out it's just the wind,"},{"time":237000,"text":"you've made an error in cognition,"},{"time":239000,"text":"made a Type I error, false positive."},{"time":241000,"text":"But no harm. You just move away."},{"time":243000,"text":"You're more cautious. You're more vigilant."},{"time":245000,"text":"On the other hand, if you believe that the rustle in the grass is just the wind,"},{"time":247000,"text":"and it turns out it's a dangerous predator,"},{"time":250000,"text":"you're lunch."},{"time":252000,"text":"You've just won a Darwin award."},{"time":254000,"text":"You've been taken out of the gene pool."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256000,"text":"Now the problem here is that"},{"time":258000,"text":"patternicities will occur whenever the cost"},{"time":260000,"text":"of making a Type I error"},{"time":262000,"text":"is less than the cost of making a Type II error."},{"time":264000,"text":"This is the only equation in the talk by the way."},{"time":266000,"text":"We have a pattern detection problem"},{"time":268000,"text":"that is assessing the difference between a Type I and a Type II error"},{"time":271000,"text":"is highly problematic,"},{"time":273000,"text":"especially in split-second, life-and-death situations."},{"time":276000,"text":"So the default position"},{"time":278000,"text":"is just: Believe all patterns are real --"},{"time":280000,"text":"All rustles in the grass are dangerous predators"},{"time":283000,"text":"and not just the wind."},{"time":285000,"text":"And so I think that we evolved ..."},{"time":287000,"text":"there was a natural selection for the propensity for our belief engines,"},{"time":290000,"text":"our pattern-seeking brain processes,"},{"time":292000,"text":"to always find meaningful patterns"},{"time":294000,"text":"and infuse them with these sort of"},{"time":296000,"text":"predatory or intentional agencies that I'll come back to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299000,"text":"So for example, what do you see here?"},{"time":301000,"text":"It's a horse head, that's right."},{"time":303000,"text":"It looks like a horse. It must be a horse."},{"time":305000,"text":"That's a pattern."},{"time":307000,"text":"And is it really a horse?"},{"time":309000,"text":"Or is it more like a frog?"},{"time":312000,"text":"See, our pattern detection device,"},{"time":314000,"text":"which appears to be located in the anterior cingulate cortex --"},{"time":317000,"text":"it's our little detection device there --"},{"time":320000,"text":"can be easily fooled, and this is the problem."},{"time":322000,"text":"For example, what do you see here?"},{"time":324000,"text":"Yes, of course, it's a cow."},{"time":327000,"text":"Once I prime the brain -- it's called cognitive priming --"},{"time":330000,"text":"once I prime the brain to see it,"},{"time":332000,"text":"it pops back out again even without the pattern that I've imposed on it."},{"time":335000,"text":"And what do you see here?"},{"time":337000,"text":"Some people see a Dalmatian dog."},{"time":339000,"text":"Yes, there it is. And there's the prime."},{"time":341000,"text":"So when I go back without the prime,"},{"time":343000,"text":"your brain already has the model"},{"time":345000,"text":"so you can see it again."},{"time":347000,"text":"What do you see here?"},{"time":350000,"text":"Planet Saturn. Yes, that's good."},{"time":352000,"text":"How about here?"},{"time":355000,"text":"Just shout out anything you see."},{"time":359000,"text":"That's a good audience, Chris."},{"time":361000,"text":"Because there's nothing in this. Well, allegedly there's nothing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":364000,"text":"This is an experiment done by Jennifer Whitson"},{"time":367000,"text":"at U.T. Austin"},{"time":369000,"text":"on corporate environments"},{"time":371000,"text":"and whether feelings of uncertainty and out of control"},{"time":374000,"text":"makes people see illusory patterns."},{"time":376000,"text":"That is, almost everybody sees the planet Saturn."},{"time":379000,"text":"People that are put in a condition of feeling out of control"},{"time":382000,"text":"are more likely to see something in this,"},{"time":384000,"text":"which is allegedly patternless."},{"time":387000,"text":"In other words, the propensity to find these patterns"},{"time":390000,"text":"goes up when there's a lack of control."},{"time":393000,"text":"For example, baseball players are notoriously superstitious"},{"time":396000,"text":"when they're batting,"},{"time":398000,"text":"but not so much when they're fielding."},{"time":400000,"text":"Because fielders are successful"},{"time":402000,"text":"90 to 95 percent of the time."},{"time":404000,"text":"The best batters fail seven out of 10 times."},{"time":407000,"text":"So their superstitions, their patternicities,"},{"time":409000,"text":"are all associated with feelings of lack of control"},{"time":412000,"text":"and so forth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":415000,"text":"What do you see in this particular one here, in this field?"},{"time":418000,"text":"Anybody see an object there?"},{"time":420000,"text":"There actually is something here,"},{"time":422000,"text":"but it's degraded."},{"time":424000,"text":"While you're thinking about that,"},{"time":426000,"text":"this was an experiment done by Susan Blackmore,"},{"time":428000,"text":"a psychologist in England,"},{"time":430000,"text":"who showed subjects this degraded image"},{"time":432000,"text":"and then ran a correlation between"},{"time":434000,"text":"their scores on an ESP test:"},{"time":436000,"text":"How much did they believe in the paranormal,"},{"time":438000,"text":"supernatural, angels and so forth."},{"time":441000,"text":"And those who scored high on the ESP scale,"},{"time":444000,"text":"tended to not only see"},{"time":446000,"text":"more patterns in the degraded images"},{"time":448000,"text":"but incorrect patterns."},{"time":450000,"text":"Here is what you show subjects."},{"time":452000,"text":"The fish is degraded 20 percent, 50 percent"},{"time":455000,"text":"and then the one I showed you,"},{"time":457000,"text":"70 percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459000,"text":"A similar experiment was done by another [Swiss] psychologist"},{"time":461000,"text":"named Peter Brugger,"},{"time":463000,"text":"who found significantly more meaningful patterns"},{"time":466000,"text":"were perceived on the right hemisphere,"},{"time":468000,"text":"via the left visual field, than the left hemisphere."},{"time":471000,"text":"So if you present subjects the images such"},{"time":473000,"text":"that it's going to end up on the right hemisphere instead of the left,"},{"time":476000,"text":"then they're more likely to see patterns"},{"time":478000,"text":"than if you put it on the left hemisphere."},{"time":480000,"text":"Our right hemisphere appears to be"},{"time":482000,"text":"where a lot of this patternicity occurs."},{"time":484000,"text":"So what we're trying to do is bore into the brain"},{"time":486000,"text":"to see where all this happens."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488000,"text":"Brugger and his colleague, Christine Mohr,"},{"time":491000,"text":"gave subjects L-DOPA."},{"time":493000,"text":"L-DOPA's a drug, as you know, given for treating Parkinson's disease,"},{"time":496000,"text":"which is related to a decrease in dopamine."},{"time":499000,"text":"L-DOPA increases dopamine."},{"time":501000,"text":"An increase of dopamine caused"},{"time":503000,"text":"subjects to see more patterns"},{"time":505000,"text":"than those that did not receive the dopamine."},{"time":507000,"text":"So dopamine appears to be the drug"},{"time":509000,"text":"associated with patternicity."},{"time":511000,"text":"In fact, neuroleptic drugs"},{"time":513000,"text":"that are used to eliminate psychotic behavior,"},{"time":515000,"text":"things like paranoia, delusions"},{"time":517000,"text":"and hallucinations,"},{"time":519000,"text":"these are patternicities."},{"time":521000,"text":"They're incorrect patterns. They're false positives. They're Type I errors."},{"time":524000,"text":"And if you give them drugs"},{"time":526000,"text":"that are dopamine antagonists,"},{"time":528000,"text":"they go away."},{"time":530000,"text":"That is, you decrease the amount of dopamine,"},{"time":532000,"text":"and their tendency to see"},{"time":534000,"text":"patterns like that decreases."},{"time":536000,"text":"On the other hand, amphetamines like cocaine"},{"time":539000,"text":"are dopamine agonists."},{"time":541000,"text":"They increase the amount of dopamine."},{"time":543000,"text":"So you're more likely to feel in a euphoric state,"},{"time":546000,"text":"creativity, find more patterns."}]},{"cues":[{"time":548000,"text":"In fact, I saw Robin Williams recently"},{"time":550000,"text":"talk about how he thought he was much funnier"},{"time":552000,"text":"when he was doing cocaine, when he had that issue, than now."},{"time":555000,"text":"So perhaps more dopamine"},{"time":557000,"text":"is related to more creativity."},{"time":559000,"text":"Dopamine, I think, changes"},{"time":561000,"text":"our signal-to-noise ratio."},{"time":563000,"text":"That is, how accurate we are"},{"time":565000,"text":"in finding patterns."},{"time":567000,"text":"If it's too low, you're more likely to make too many Type II errors."},{"time":570000,"text":"You miss the real patterns. You don't want to be too skeptical."},{"time":572000,"text":"If you're too skeptical, you'll miss the really interesting good ideas."},{"time":576000,"text":"Just right, you're creative, and yet you don't fall for too much baloney."},{"time":579000,"text":"Too high and maybe you see patterns everywhere."},{"time":582000,"text":"Every time somebody looks at you, you think people are staring at you."},{"time":585000,"text":"You think people are talking about you."},{"time":587000,"text":"And if you go too far on that, that's just simply"},{"time":589000,"text":"labeled as madness."},{"time":591000,"text":"It's a distinction perhaps we might make"},{"time":593000,"text":"between two Nobel laureates, Richard Feynman"},{"time":595000,"text":"and John Nash."},{"time":597000,"text":"One sees maybe just the right number"},{"time":599000,"text":"of patterns to win a Nobel Prize."},{"time":601000,"text":"The other one also, but maybe too many patterns."},{"time":603000,"text":"And we then call that schizophrenia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":606000,"text":"So the signal-to-noise ratio then presents us with a pattern-detection problem."},{"time":609000,"text":"And of course you all know exactly"},{"time":611000,"text":"what this is, right?"},{"time":613000,"text":"And what pattern do you see here?"},{"time":615000,"text":"Again, I'm putting your anterior cingulate cortex to the test here,"},{"time":618000,"text":"causing you conflicting pattern detections."},{"time":621000,"text":"You know, of course, this is Via Uno shoes."},{"time":623000,"text":"These are sandals."},{"time":626000,"text":"Pretty sexy feet, I must say."},{"time":629000,"text":"Maybe a little Photoshopped."},{"time":631000,"text":"And of course, the ambiguous figures"},{"time":633000,"text":"that seem to flip-flop back and forth."},{"time":635000,"text":"It turns out what you're thinking about a lot"},{"time":637000,"text":"influences what you"},{"time":639000,"text":"tend to see."},{"time":641000,"text":"And you see the lamp here, I know."},{"time":643000,"text":"Because the lights on here."},{"time":646000,"text":"Of course, thanks to the environmentalist movement"},{"time":648000,"text":"we're all sensitive to the plight of marine mammals."},{"time":651000,"text":"So what you see in this particular ambiguous figure"},{"time":654000,"text":"is, of course, the dolphins, right?"},{"time":656000,"text":"You see a dolphin here,"},{"time":658000,"text":"and there's a dolphin,"},{"time":660000,"text":"and there's a dolphin."},{"time":662000,"text":"That's a dolphin tail there, guys."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":670000,"text":"If we can give you conflicting data, again,"},{"time":673000,"text":"your ACC is going to be going into hyperdrive."},{"time":676000,"text":"If you look down here, it's fine. If you look up here, then you get conflicting data."},{"time":679000,"text":"And then we have to flip the image"},{"time":681000,"text":"for you to see that it's a set up."},{"time":685000,"text":"The impossible crate illusion."},{"time":687000,"text":"It's easy to fool the brain in 2D."},{"time":689000,"text":"So you say, \"Aw, come on Shermer, anybody can do that"},{"time":691000,"text":"in a Psych 101 text with an illusion like that.\""},{"time":693000,"text":"Well here's the late, great Jerry Andrus'"},{"time":695000,"text":"\"impossible crate\" illusion in 3D,"},{"time":698000,"text":"in which Jerry is standing inside"},{"time":700000,"text":"the impossible crate."},{"time":702000,"text":"And he was kind enough to post this"},{"time":704000,"text":"and give us the reveal."},{"time":706000,"text":"Of course, camera angle is everything. The photographer is over there,"},{"time":709000,"text":"and this board appears to overlap with this one, and this one with that one, and so on."},{"time":712000,"text":"But even when I take it away,"},{"time":714000,"text":"the illusion is so powerful because of how are brains are wired"},{"time":716000,"text":"to find those certain kinds of patterns."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719000,"text":"This is a fairly new one"},{"time":721000,"text":"that throws us off because of the conflicting patterns"},{"time":723000,"text":"of comparing this angle with that angle."},{"time":726000,"text":"In fact, it's the exact same picture side by side."},{"time":729000,"text":"So what you're doing is comparing that angle"},{"time":731000,"text":"instead of with this one, but with that one."},{"time":733000,"text":"And so your brain is fooled."},{"time":735000,"text":"Yet again, your pattern detection devices are fooled."}]},{"cues":[{"time":737000,"text":"Faces are easy to see"},{"time":739000,"text":"because we have an additional evolved"},{"time":741000,"text":"facial recognition software"},{"time":743000,"text":"in our temporal lobes."},{"time":746000,"text":"Here's some faces on the side of a rock."},{"time":749000,"text":"I'm actually not even sure if this is -- this might be Photoshopped."},{"time":752000,"text":"But anyway, the point is still made."},{"time":754000,"text":"Now which one of these looks odd to you?"},{"time":756000,"text":"In a quick reaction, which one looks odd?"},{"time":758000,"text":"The one on the left. Okay. So I'll rotate it"},{"time":760000,"text":"so it'll be the one on the right."},{"time":762000,"text":"And you are correct."},{"time":764000,"text":"A fairly famous illusion -- it was first done with Margaret Thatcher."},{"time":767000,"text":"Now, they trade up the politicians every time."},{"time":769000,"text":"Well, why is this happening?"},{"time":771000,"text":"Well, we know exactly where it happens,"},{"time":773000,"text":"in the temporal lobe, right across, sort of above your ear there,"},{"time":776000,"text":"in a little structure called the fusiform gyrus."},{"time":779000,"text":"And there's two types of cells that do this,"},{"time":781000,"text":"that record facial features either globally,"},{"time":784000,"text":"or specifically these large, rapid-firing cells,"},{"time":786000,"text":"first look at the general face."},{"time":788000,"text":"So you recognize Obama immediately."},{"time":790000,"text":"And then you notice something quite"},{"time":792000,"text":"a little bit odd about the eyes and the mouth."},{"time":794000,"text":"Especially when they're upside down,"},{"time":796000,"text":"you're engaging that general facial recognition software there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":799000,"text":"Now I said back in our little thought experiment,"},{"time":802000,"text":"you're a hominid walking on the plains of Africa."},{"time":804000,"text":"Is it just the wind or a dangerous predator?"},{"time":807000,"text":"What's the difference between those?"},{"time":809000,"text":"Well, the wind is inanimate;"},{"time":811000,"text":"the dangerous predator is an intentional agent."},{"time":813000,"text":"And I call this process agenticity."},{"time":815000,"text":"That is the tendency to infuse patterns"},{"time":817000,"text":"with meaning, intention and agency,"},{"time":819000,"text":"often invisible beings from the top down."},{"time":822000,"text":"This is an idea that we got"},{"time":824000,"text":"from a fellow TEDster here, Dan Dennett,"},{"time":826000,"text":"who talked about taking the intentional stance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":828000,"text":"So it's a type of that expanded to explain, I think, a lot of different things:"},{"time":831000,"text":"souls, spirits, ghosts, gods, demons, angels,"},{"time":834000,"text":"aliens, intelligent designers,"},{"time":836000,"text":"government conspiracists"},{"time":838000,"text":"and all manner of invisible agents"},{"time":840000,"text":"with power and intention, are believed"},{"time":842000,"text":"to haunt our world and control our lives."},{"time":844000,"text":"I think it's the basis of animism"},{"time":846000,"text":"and polytheism and monotheism."},{"time":849000,"text":"It's the belief that aliens are somehow"},{"time":851000,"text":"more advanced than us, more moral than us,"},{"time":853000,"text":"and the narratives always are"},{"time":855000,"text":"that they're coming here to save us and rescue us from on high."},{"time":858000,"text":"The intelligent designer's always portrayed"},{"time":860000,"text":"as this super intelligent, moral being"},{"time":863000,"text":"that comes down to design life."},{"time":865000,"text":"Even the idea that government can rescue us --"},{"time":867000,"text":"that's no longer the wave of the future,"},{"time":869000,"text":"but that is, I think, a type of agenticity:"},{"time":871000,"text":"projecting somebody up there,"},{"time":873000,"text":"big and powerful, will come rescue us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":875000,"text":"And this is also, I think, the basis of conspiracy theories."},{"time":877000,"text":"There's somebody hiding behind there pulling the strings,"},{"time":880000,"text":"whether it's the Illuminati"},{"time":882000,"text":"or the Bilderbergers."},{"time":884000,"text":"But this is a pattern detection problem, isn't it?"},{"time":886000,"text":"Some patterns are real and some are not."},{"time":888000,"text":"Was JFK assassinated by a conspiracy or by a lone assassin?"},{"time":891000,"text":"Well, if you go there -- there's people there on any given day --"},{"time":894000,"text":"like when I went there, here -- showing me where the different shooters were."},{"time":897000,"text":"My favorite one was he was in the manhole."},{"time":900000,"text":"And he popped out at the last second, took that shot."},{"time":903000,"text":"But of course, Lincoln was assassinated by a conspiracy."},{"time":905000,"text":"So we can't just uniformly dismiss"},{"time":907000,"text":"all patterns like that."},{"time":909000,"text":"Because, let's face it, some patterns are real."},{"time":911000,"text":"Some conspiracies really are true."},{"time":915000,"text":"Explains a lot, maybe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":917000,"text":"And 9/11 has a conspiracy theory. It is a conspiracy."},{"time":920000,"text":"We did a whole issue on it."},{"time":922000,"text":"Nineteen members of Al Queda plotting to fly planes into buildings"},{"time":924000,"text":"constitutes a conspiracy."},{"time":926000,"text":"But that's not what the \"9/11 truthers\" think."},{"time":928000,"text":"They think it was an inside job by the Bush administration."},{"time":931000,"text":"Well, that's a whole other lecture."},{"time":933000,"text":"You know how we know that 9/11"},{"time":935000,"text":"was not orchestrated by the Bush administration?"},{"time":937000,"text":"Because it worked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":939000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":942000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":945000,"text":"So we are natural-born dualists."},{"time":947000,"text":"Our agenticity process comes from"},{"time":949000,"text":"the fact that we can enjoy movies like these."},{"time":951000,"text":"Because we can imagine, in essence,"},{"time":953000,"text":"continuing on."},{"time":955000,"text":"We know that if you stimulate the temporal lobe,"},{"time":957000,"text":"you can produce a feeling of out-of-body experiences,"},{"time":959000,"text":"near-death experiences,"},{"time":961000,"text":"which you can do by just touching an electrode to the temporal lobe there."},{"time":964000,"text":"Or you can do it through loss of consciousness,"},{"time":966000,"text":"by accelerating in a centrifuge."},{"time":968000,"text":"You get a hypoxia, or a lower oxygen."},{"time":971000,"text":"And the brain then senses"},{"time":973000,"text":"that there's an out-of-body experience."},{"time":975000,"text":"You can use -- which I did, went out and did --"},{"time":977000,"text":"Michael Persinger's God Helmet,"},{"time":979000,"text":"that bombards your temporal lobes with electromagnetic waves."},{"time":981000,"text":"And you get a sense of out-of-body experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":984000,"text":"So I'm going to end here with a short video clip"},{"time":986000,"text":"that sort of brings all this together."},{"time":988000,"text":"It's just a minute and a half."},{"time":990000,"text":"It ties together all this into the power of expectation and the power of belief."},{"time":993000,"text":"Go ahead and roll it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":995000,"text":"Narrator: This is the venue they chose for their fake auditions"},{"time":998000,"text":"for an advert for lip balm."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1000000,"text":"Woman: We're hoping we can use part of this"},{"time":1002000,"text":"in a national commercial, right?"},{"time":1004000,"text":"And this is test on some lip balms"},{"time":1006000,"text":"that we have over here."},{"time":1008000,"text":"And these are our models who are going to help us,"},{"time":1010000,"text":"Roger and Matt."},{"time":1012000,"text":"And we have our own lip balm,"},{"time":1014000,"text":"and we have a leading brand."},{"time":1016000,"text":"Would you have any problem"},{"time":1018000,"text":"kissing our models to test it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1020000,"text":"Girl: No."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1022000,"text":"Woman: You wouldn't? (Girl: No.) Woman: You'd think that was fine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1024000,"text":"Girl: That would be fine. (Woman: Okay.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1026000,"text":"So this is a blind test."},{"time":1029000,"text":"I'm going to ask you to go ahead"},{"time":1031000,"text":"and put a blindfold on."},{"time":1034000,"text":"Kay, now can you see anything? (Girl: No.)"},{"time":1037000,"text":"Pull it so you can't even see down. (Girl: Okay.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1039000,"text":"Woman: It's completely blind now, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1041000,"text":"Girl: Yes. (Woman: Okay.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1043000,"text":"Now, what I'm going to be looking for in this test"},{"time":1046000,"text":"is how it protects your lips,"},{"time":1049000,"text":"the texture, right,"},{"time":1051000,"text":"and maybe if you can discern any flavor or not."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1054000,"text":"Girl: Okay. (Woman: Have you ever done a kissing test before?)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1057000,"text":"Girl: No."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1059000,"text":"Woman: Take a step here."},{"time":1061000,"text":"Okay, now I'm going to ask you to pucker up."},{"time":1063000,"text":"Pucker up big and lean in just a little bit, okay?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1071000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1075000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1084000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1095000,"text":"Woman: Okay."},{"time":1097000,"text":"And, Jennifer, how did that feel?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1099000,"text":"Jennifer: Good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1101000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1108000,"text":"Girl: Oh my God!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1110000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1115000,"text":"Michael Shermer: Thank you very much. Thank you. Thanks."}]}]}